**`src/routes/posts.ts`** - Full CRUD operations:
- `GET /posts` - List all posts
- `GET /posts/:id` - Get single post
- `POST /posts` - Create post (requires title, content; userId defaults to 1)
- `PUT /posts/:id` - Update post (partial update for title/content)
- `DELETE /posts/:id` - Delete post

**`src/routes/comments.ts`** - Full CRUD operations:
- `GET /posts/:postId/comments` - List comments for a post
- `GET /comments/:id` - Get single comment
- `POST /posts/:postId/comments` - Create comment (requires body; userId defaults to 1)
- `PUT /comments/:id` - Update comment
- `DELETE /comments/:id` - Delete comment

### 4. **Existing Middleware**

**`src/middleware/logger.ts`** - Simple request logging middleware:
```typescript
import { Request, Response, NextFunction } from "express";

export function logger(req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {
  const start = Date.now();
  res.on("finish", () => {
    const duration = Date.now() - start;
    console.log(`${req.method} ${req.path} ${res.statusCode} - ${duration}ms`);
  });
  next();
}
```

Currently only logs request method, path, status code, and duration.

