---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Global Request augmentation (`declare global`) | Cleanest TypeScript pattern; avoids casting in every route handler |
| `crypto.createHash("sha256")` for passwords | Task forbids bcrypt; Node built-in, no extra dependency |
| `JWT_SECRET` exported from middleware, imported by auth route | Single source of truth; avoids magic string duplication |
| Seed users' plaintext passwords in `db.ts` kept as-is | No auth test logs in with seed users; login tests create fresh users via `/register` first |
| `PUT /comments/:id` also protected | Task spec says "Protect POST/PUT/DELETE"; no existing test breaks |

---

## Compatibility Notes

- All imports use `.js` extension (required by `"module": "Node16"` in tsconfig)
- `"esModuleInterop": true` allows default import of `jwt` from `jsonwebtoken`
- GET routes on `/posts` and `/posts/:postId/comments` and `/comments/:id` remain completely unmodified → existing tests in `posts.test.ts` and `comments.test.ts` continue to pass

